9 receive a North Dakota scholarship if the student:
10 1. Completed an individual consultative process or a nine-week course under
11 subsection 2 of section 15.1-21-18;
12 2. Completed the civics test under section 15.1-21-27;
13 3. Completed a four-year rolling plan, as determined by the superintendent of public
14 instruction;
15 4. Obtained a cumulative grade point average of at least 3.0 on a 4.0 grading scale, or
16 an equivalent course proficiency score if the student was enrolled in a school district
17 participating in an approved innovative education program under section 15.1-06-08.2
18 and the school district obtained a waiver under section 15.1-06-08.1;
19 5. Completed the requirements in at least four of the following while enrolled in grades
20 nine through twelve:
21 a. Twenty-five hours of community service;
22 b. A ninety-five percent attendance rate as determined under section 15.1-20-02.1,
23 not including any school-related absences;
